    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thompson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Gresham directs Mr. Thompson to induce, by cooperation with the commanding
                    officer of the forces of the United States, and if possible with others, the
                    insurgents to designate a place, if such a place can be found, at which vessels
                    of neutral nations may, without interfering with mililitary operations, take and
                    discharge cargoes in safety.</p>
            </div>
